parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft can cause the engine to stall or shut down, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts down
the vehicle loses power
the crankshaft breaks or cracks
the timing belt pulley drops
and the vehicle may experience a strong smell of fuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts down
the vehicle loses power
the check engine light comes on
and the vehicle may experience a strong smell of fuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt can cause the engine to stall or shut down, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The timing belt breaks or cracks
the engine stalls or shuts down
the vehicle loses power
and the check engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel system issues can cause the vehicle to experience a strong smell of fuel, which can be a fire hazard.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a strong smell of fuel
the fuel tank vent hose is faulty
and the fuel injection system is malfunctioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine fails
the vehicle loses power
and the check engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system leaks and failures can cause fuel to leak onto the engine or other components, leading to a fire hazard, and may also cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of an accident.
symptoms: Strong fuel odor inside the vehicle
fuel leaks from under the tank
fuel leaks from fuel lines
fuel pump failure
fuel gauge erratic behavior
sudden loss of power or stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel pump failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, increasing the risk of an accident, and may also cause fuel leaks, leading to a fire hazard.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power or stalling
fuel pump failure
humming sound from the fuel tank
no pump start-up at engine start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front-passenger-side lap belt retractor can cause the seat belt to jam, preventing it from extending properly, which can lead to accidents or injuries in the event of sudden stops or crashes.
symptoms: The seat belt will not extend more than 8-12 inches
the ratchet mechanism "catches" and prevents the seat belt from reaching the buckle
the seat belt seizes up after retracting
the seat belt only extends fully for a one-time use before seizing up again.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the driver's side seat belt can cause the seat belt to become inoperative, preventing it from restraining the driver in the event of sudden stops or crashes, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seat belt will not move
the seat belt jumps out of place/rattles while driving
the seat belt does not stay stationary
the seat belt will not lock.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shoulder harness can cause tears or damage to the harness, which can lead to accidents or injuries in the event of sudden stops or crashes.
symptoms: The shoulder harness develops tears intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seat belt can cause the seat belt to become entangled or caught around the occupant's neck, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear shoulder/lap belt caught a child around the neck and entangled when attempting to exit.
